<document xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0"
          xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
          xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/xdoc-2.0.xsd">

    <properties>
        <title>Using the Chain Service Factory</title>
    </properties>

    <body>
        <section name="Using the Chain Service Factory">

            <p>This example demonstrates the use of the Chain service factory.</p>
            <subsection name="Module Descriptor">
                <p>The following shows a module descriptor for a service consisting of a command chain used to classify the
                    kind of animal being passed in as a parameter.</p>
                <p>The chain consists of 6 commands, each one classifying the paramter specified into one of each of
                    the following categories:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fish</li>
                    <li>Birds</li>
                    <li>Mammals</li>
                    <li>Vertabrates</li>
                    <li>Insects</li>
                    <li>Invertabrates</li>
                </ul>

                <macro name="snippet">
                    <param name="id" value="full"/>
                    <param name="url" value="http://codestat.ops4j.org/browse/~raw,r=HEAD/OPS4J/projects/gaderian/examples/src/main/resources/org/ops4j/gaderian/examples/chain/chain.xml"/>
                </macro>

            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Service Interface">

                <p>Below is the service interface, defining the <code>classify</code> method.</p>

                <macro name="snippet">

                    <param name="id" value="full"/>
                    <param name="url"
                           value="http://codestat.ops4j.org/browse/~raw,r=HEAD/OPS4J/projects/gaderian/examples/src/main/java/org/ops4j/gaderian/examples/chain/AnimalClassifier.java"/>
                </macro>

            </subsection>

        </section>
    </body>
</document>
